author: The Associated Press
title: Trade deal reached among U.S., 11 Pacific Rim countries
text: Trade deal reached among U.S., 11 Pacific Rim countries Trans-Pacific Partnership FILE - In this Nov. 10, 2014 file photo, U.S. President Barack Obama, center, speaks during his meeting with leaders of the Trans-Pacific Partnership countries, in Beijing. The United States and 11 other Pacific Rim countries on Monday, Oct. 5, 2015, agreed to the Trans-Pacific Partnership. The White House says the agreement will eliminate tariffs on all made-in-America manufactured goods exported to TPP countries. (AP Photo/Pablo Martinez Monsivais, File)
